cards.body:
Theory only until you run this once. Then the console Usage tab will move off zero.

              Step 1 - set key in PowerShell (session only)

              $env:XAI_API_KEY = "paste-your-key-here"
              Step 2 - send one request

              $body = @{
  model = "grok-4.3"
  input = @(
    @{ role = "user"; content = "Reply with exactly: API works." }
  )
} | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5

Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "https://api.x.ai/v1/responses" -Method POST -Headers @{
  "Authorization" = "Bearer $env:XAI_API_KEY"
  "Content-Type"  = "application/json"
} -Body $body
              What you should see

              PowerShell prints an object. Look for output text containing API works. Refresh console.x.ai - Requests should show 1, usage a fraction of a cent.


                What you learned from one call

                The entire API pattern: auth header + JSON body → remote model → JSON response → money deducted. Every product (voice, images, bots) is a variation on this.
